<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="135" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,405,502]" pageId="2" pageNumber="135">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,441,466]" pageId="2" pageNumber="135">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The male of 
<taxonomicName box="[470,738,441,466]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Brachypogon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="135" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="freidbergi">
<emphasis box="[470,738,441,466]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="135">Brachypogon freidbergi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinct in having elongate slender apicolateral processes of tergite 
<number box="[229,245,478,502]" pageId="2" pageNumber="135" value="9.0">9</number>
, and a deeply forked Y-shaped gonostylus that resembles obtuse crayfish claws. Females are unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
